==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Innoxious
<hw>In*nox"ious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>innoxius</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and <er>Noxious</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Free from hurtful qualities or effects; harmless;
innocuous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Innoxious</xex> flames.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir
K. Digby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Free from crime; pure; innocent.</def>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In*nox`ious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>In*nox"ious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Innubilous</ent>⟦br⟧
